---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Weather App | Sam Popham">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Weather Reporter</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      A desktop weather application built in Python using PyQt6 and the OpenWeather API.
      The app allows users to search for multiple locations at once and presents current
      weather conditions in a clean, card-based interface with responsive layout and
      keyboard-friendly input.
    </p>

    <img
      src="/images/weather.png"
      alt="Weather Reporter application showing multiple weather cards"
      class="rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8"
    />

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Key Features</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
      <li>Multi-location search with country code validation</li>
      <li>Keyboard-navigable autocomplete for city input</li>
      <li>Asynchronous API requests using worker threads</li>
      <li>Metric and imperial unit switching</li>
      <li>Card-based UI displaying temperature, wind, humidity, pressure, and sunrise/sunset</li>
      <li>Consistent custom colour palette and accessible visual design</li>
    </ul>

    <a
      href="https://github.com/SPopham1/python-weather-app"
      target="_blank"
      class="inline-block mt-4 text-blue-600 hover:underline"
    >
      View on GitHub â†’
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>
